# Project Rules for KiloCode AI Template

## Directory Structure

- PRD goes in `PRD/<PRD-ID>-<name>/` (feature folder with PRD + tasks)
- Completed PRDs go in `PRD/done/`
- Architecture Decision Records go in `PRD/adr/`
- KiloCode configuration lives in `.kilocode/`
- Workflows live in `.kilocode/workflows/`
- Skills live in `.kilocode/skills/`

## Workflow Enforcement

### New Features
- Every new feature MUST start with the **Feature Planning Workflow** (`.kilocode/workflows/feature-planning.md`)
- No coding should begin without an approved PRD in `PRD/<PRD-ID>-<name>/`
- PRDs MUST have measurable acceptance criteria

### Implementation
- Use the **Implementation Workflow** (`.kilocode/workflows/implementation.md`) to break PRDs into tasks
- Every task MUST follow the **Coding & QA Workflow** (`.kilocode/workflows/coding-qa.md`)
- No task is complete without passing SonarQube quality gates

### Quality Gates
- All code must pass SonarQube analysis with no new BLOCKER or HIGH issues
- Unit test coverage must be >80% for business logic
- Security-sensitive code must pass Security mode review
- All acceptance criteria must be verified before task completion

## Coding Standards

- Write clean, readable code with meaningful names
- Follow the language's idiomatic conventions
- Include error handling for all external interactions
- Document public APIs and complex logic
- No hardcoded secrets or environment-specific values
- Use structured logging with context
- Use conventional commits (feat:, fix:, docs:, refactor:, test:, chore:)

## File Organization

- Keep files focused and single-purpose
- Follow the project's established directory structure
- Name files descriptively using the project's naming conventions
- PRD folders follow: `<PRD-ID>-<short-name>/`
- Task files follow: `TASK-<PRD-ID>-<SEQ>-<short-description>.md`

## Mode Handoff Protocol

- Frontend/Backend/Mobile/Database → QA (for testing)
- Frontend/Backend/Mobile → Security (if auth/input/sensitive data involved)
- All implementation modes → Documentation (for API docs, component docs)
- DevOps → QA (verify CI pipeline runs tests)
- DevOps → Security (review infrastructure security)
- All modes → Orchestrator (report completion)
